  "conformsToProfile": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileMinimal",
  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. The model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5 across the clinical operating envelope (flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM). Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification propagates inlet boundary-condition variability and blood viscosity uncertainty. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are addressed; 7 were formally assessed and 6 were scoped out as epistemic gaps acknowledged at MRL 5. The requirement binding this assurance unit specifies that predicted hemolysis index shall not exceed 0.8% normalized index of hemolysis under worst-case operating conditions, consistent with FDA guidance on blood-contacting devices. Sufficient evidence was assembled to support a Minimal-profile acceptance decision for submission planning purposes.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-nih-limit",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-vad-class3",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-piv-experimental",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-in-vitro-validation",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-mc-uncertainty-samples-5000"
  ],
  "hasValidationResult": [
